You are building Abyssal Forge, a 3D dark-fantasy browser RPG for the Cursor Vibe Jam 2026.

TECH STACK:
- Client: Babylon.js 7, React 18, Zustand 4, Vite 5, TypeScript 5 strict
- Server: Colyseus 0.15, Node.js 20, Express 4
- Data: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Realtime) [Phase 2+]

CODING RULES:
1. Never use `any`. All types must come from /shared/types/.
2. All game constants live in /shared/constants/. Never hardcode values.
3. Game logic (damage, loot rolls, XP) must be duplicated on server for authority.
4. Client systems are for display and prediction only. Server is truth.
5. Every Zustand store uses the slice pattern with selectors.
6. Every Babylon.js mesh must be disposed when scene unloads to prevent memory leaks.
7. All Supabase queries use RLS-protected endpoints. Never bypass RLS.
8. Colyseus message types must be typed with a discriminated union.
9. Use framer-motion for all UI transitions. No CSS transitions for game UI.
10. All async functions are async/await with try/catch. No promise chains.

FILE HEADERS: Every file must start with:
/**
 * @description [what this file does]
 * @author Abyssal Forge
 * @version 1.0.0
 */

AESTHETIC RULES:
- Dark background: #0D0D0F
- Primary accent: #A855F7 (purple)
- Secondary accent: #EF4444 (red)
- Text primary: #F9FAFB
- Text secondary: #6B7280
- Glassmorphism: backdrop-filter: blur(12px), background: rgba(255,255,255,0.04)
- Fonts: 'Inter' for UI, 'JetBrains Mono' for numbers/stats
- All hit numbers, XP gains, damage must have a pop animation (scale 1→1.2→1 over 150ms)

COMPETITION RULES (Vibe Jam 2026):
- Widget snippet MUST be in index.html at all times
- NO loading screens — all assets must be procedural (Babylon.js primitives only)
- Game must be instantly playable with no login/signup
- Guest name auto-generated (e.g. VoidWalker#4821) — no username prompt
- Portal webring exit/entry must be functional
